Instead of faking an import you can simply tell Angular to provide your fake service when the real one is requested. A [StackBlitz](https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-lp634h?file=src/app/app.module.ts) as an example.

in `app.module.ts` in the `providers`:

    @NgModule({
      imports:      [ BrowserModule, FormsModule ],
      declarations: [ AppComponent ],
      bootstrap:    [ AppComponent ],
      providers: [
        {
          provide: RealService,
          useClass: FakeService
        }
      ]
    })
    export class AppModule { }

Now every time the RealService is requested the fake service will be served instead.

